      "kwargs": {
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "{\"success\":true,\"process_rule_id\":\"J09A\",\"process_rule\":\"1. Make a copy of decision_table with TOURS starting with J09A named J09A_temp\\n2. Update the table with an additional empty column ENTSCHEIDUNG\\n3. Apply the following rules to the joined table:\\n   1. Count the number of EQUNR for every HAUS and set ENTSCHEIDUNG to \\\"KSA\\\" if there are less than 3 EQUNR. ELSE set ENTSCHEIDUNG to \\\"EVU\\\"\\n   2. Set all houses with HOUSE_NUM1 of 0 to \\\"EVU\\\"\\n   3. Set all houses with HOUSE_NUM1 500 - 599 to \\\"EVU\\\"\\n   4. Set all houses with HOUSE_NUM1 900 - 999 to \\\"EVU\\\"\\n4. Join this table with the EABLG table using INSTALLATION\\n5. Join this table with the NET_MASTER table and the SALES_MASTER table using EQUNR\\n6. Compare sales data and net data for these IDs:\\n   - If sales data is there, take sales data and empty net data\\n   - Otherwise stay with net data and empty sales data\\n7. Export the final data from the table as CSV file named J09A including the columns: `Meter Reading (MR) Doc. No.`, `HAUS`, `ANLAGE`, `ME_MA_ID`, `EQUNR`, `HOUSE_NUM1`, `ENTSCHEIDUNG`, `TITLE`, `FORENAME`, `SURNAME`, `STREET`, `STREETNO`, `POST_CODE1`, `CITY1`, `CITY2`, `EMAIL`\\n8. Send them to the EVU team to meter.readings@evu.com\\n9. Delete the temporary table after exporting the data\"}",
            "id": "lc_9c0389d0-cf16-42ba-b868-f9342116d156"
          }
        ],
        "type": "tool",
        "name": "retrieve_process",
        "id": "c9cfca15-89ed-4652-a4de-2c2b79784c00",
        "tool_call_id": "call_hver5rN8g4BRsvzoqjdM4QQW",
        "artifact": {
          "structured_content": {
            "success": true,
            "process_rule_id": "J09A",
            "process_rule": "1. Make a copy of decision_table with TOURS starting with J09A named J09A_temp\n2. Update the table with an additional empty column ENTSCHEIDUNG\n3. Apply the following rules to the joined table:\n   1. Count the number of EQUNR for every HAUS and set ENTSCHEIDUNG to \"KSA\" if there are less than 3 EQUNR. ELSE set ENTSCHEIDUNG to \"EVU\"\n   2. Set all houses with HOUSE_NUM1 of 0 to \"EVU\"\n   3. Set all houses with HOUSE_NUM1 500 - 599 to \"EVU\"\n   4. Set all houses with HOUSE_NUM1 900 - 999 to \"EVU\"\n4. Join this table with the EABLG table using INSTALLATION\n5. Join this table with the NET_MASTER table and the SALES_MASTER table using EQUNR\n6. Compare sales data and net data for these IDs:\n   - If sales data is there, take sales data and empty net data\n   - Otherwise stay with net data and empty sales data\n7. Export the final data from the table as CSV file named J09A including the columns: `Meter Reading (MR) Doc. No.`, `HAUS`, `ANLAGE`, `ME_MA_ID`, `EQUNR`, `HOUSE_NUM1`, `ENTSCHEIDUNG`, `TITLE`, `FORENAME`, `SURNAME`, `STREET`, `STREETNO`, `POST_CODE1`, `CITY1`, `CITY2`, `EMAIL`\n8. Send them to the EVU team to meter.readings@evu.com\n9. Delete the temporary table after exporting the data"
          }
        },
        "status": "success"
      }
    },
